<item>
            <title>[SOLR-10471] Solr script always sets zkClientTimeout to 15000 if ZK_CLIENT_TIMEOUT unset</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-10471</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Per &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5565&quot; title=&quot;Raise default ZooKeeper session timeout to 30 seconds from 15 seconds.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-5565&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-5565&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, ZooKeeper session timeout should have been raised to 30s. This was changed in the solr.xml example but it was not changed in the solr script, which has this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; [ -z &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;$ZK_CLIENT_TIMEOUT&quot;&lt;/span&gt; ]; then
    ZK_CLIENT_TIMEOUT=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;15000&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
  fi
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And for solr.cmd:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt; IF &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;%ZK_CLIENT_TIMEOUT%&quot;&lt;/span&gt;==&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&quot; set &quot;&lt;/span&gt;ZK_CLIENT_TIMEOUT=15000&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So regardless of what is in solr.xml, if ZK_CLIENT_TIMEOUT is not set, it will be overridden to 15,000. I&apos;d think this should be raised to 30,000 or removed entirely to fall back on the solr.xml&apos;s behavior.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=markrmiller%40gmail.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;markrmiller@gmail.com&quot;&gt;markrmiller@gmail.com&lt;/a&gt; is this correct?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
